Overview
Over Q1 and into Q2 2026, I led a comprehensive modernisation of the BISS (Basic Income Support for Sustainability) test automation framework, transforming it from a brittle, hand-maintained suite of 135+ hard-coded test scripts into a self-service, data-driven, self-healing regression engine. This improvement directly addresses engineering quality, team productivity, and risk reduction in government-critical payment-validation processes.

Problem Identified
The legacy automation suite exhibited critical structural defects:

• 90+ copy-pasted login blocks — any login flow change required editing dozens of files by hand
• 300+ hard-coded herd numbers and person names — tests broke when data was exhausted; sensitive PII sat in comments (data-governance risk)
• ~40% dead code — obsolete commented-out steps shipped every run, eroding confidence
• Placeholder assertions — verification steps checked against masked values that could never fail, giving false-positive passes
• Zero resilience — a single flaky request or expired login halted the entire run; no recovery
• Manual data preparation — someone had to maintain a spreadsheet of valid test herds before each run
• No scheduled execution — results were ad-hoc; no nightly confidence baseline for the business
Solution Implemented
1. Data-Driven Architecture (No Hard-Coded Test Records)
Built a two-database routing layer (DBRouter) querying live Oracle DATA and iNet schemas at startup. The @BeforeAll bootstrap automatically selects a valid herd, shuffles candidates, validates the owning agent, and resolves the pair before any scenario runs. Tests declare intent ("open a dashboard using herd data") — the framework sources the actual herd at runtime.

• Result: Every run gets fresh data; nothing goes stale; zero manual spreadsheet maintenance.
2. Business-Language Tests (Readable, Auditable, Maintainable)
Migrated 135+ imperative "Agent Click / Fill / Select" scripts into declarative Gherkin scenarios describing the BISS process in plain language. Each scenario chains a complete business flow (login → navigation → data entry → submission) into a coherent narrative.

• Result: Analysts and compliance officers can read tests without developer translation; coverage is audit-traceable to Jira.
3. Self-Healing & Resilience (6-Layer Recovery)
Implemented a graduated recovery system:

1. Smart waits using FluentWait & WaitStrategy enums — no Thread.sleep()
2. Angular Material dropdown self-heal — standard select → root FluentWait → overlay-portal fallback
3. Expired-login recovery — detects SSO expiry, marks agent expired, re-queries database, retries automatically
4. Blacklist & re-fetch — skip used herds, draw next candidate (up to 15 retries)
5. Scenario-level retry — RetryAnalyser re-runs flaky scenarios before failing
6. Soft assertions — collect failures, report together; maximise coverage per run
• Result: Real failures (network, expired logins, data contention) no longer stop the run; self-recovery is automatic.
4. Centralised Locator Repository (405 Shared Keys)
Consolidated all UI selectors (405 locator keys) into ObjectRepository.properties. Built LocatorHarvester to auto-scan the DOM, generate validated XPaths with confidence scoring, and merge with curated locators. Tests never hold a raw XPath.

• Result: A screen change means one edit, not 50+; test maintenance time collapses.
5. Professional Reporting (4 Formats)
Every nightly run produces:

• HTML Executive Dashboard — pass/fail donut, drill-down to failing step with screenshot
• Word Evidence Documents — step-by-step screenshots embedded via Apache POI (government audit trail)
• JUnit XML — machine-readable for Jenkins trend analysis
• Post-Run Email — styled summary sent to stakeholders automatically
• Result: Stakeholders see results in their inbox each morning; no one asks "how did it go?"
6. Automated Scheduling (Nightly on Jenkins/OpenShift)
Committed Jenkinsfile with Maven execution and cron trigger (22:00 Mon–Fri). Results visible on build dashboard. Post-execution email and HTML report publishing integrated.

• Result: Confidence baseline every morning; zero manual execution needed.
